Along the lines of your inquiry:

@SamEthanMathew We have unknowingly participated in the X-Y problem

Would you like to continue looking for alternative solutions…or would you like to actually troubleshoot the problem you are experiencing? As mentioned by @j.e other teams (mine included) have successfully used various Pololu DC-DC converters (the D36V50F5 is popular) to power the OrangePi5 and Raspberry Pi5 (in 2024 for my team, earlier years for other teams) without issue - you may have selected a converter that doesn’t meet the requirements or have a wiring issue we could help troubleshoot instead of searching for an alternative solution for you to spend more money when it may be simply mis-wired, be experiencing a wiring connection problem, or be overloaded with devices if you are hooking up multiple 5V devices.
